<!--
The always-socket perceive-act agent, shared verbatim by every stage (`<Template src>`d
by main-v1/main-v2/main-v3). It is a socket server whose capability routes forward over the
socket to whichever client serves them (`interpret-photo` stays here on the brain and
calls `take-photo`; `speak-text`/`set-emotion` go to the head, `apply-heading` to the
body), bound by the `whoami` handshake as each client connects. Only the *clients* differ
between stages, so this block never changes: v1 mocks head+body, v2 swaps a wgpu fox for
the body, v3 serves a wasm head and lets a device body connect.

`{Repeat}` loops the thread endlessly, so the robot keeps perceiving and acting until the
process is killed (Ctrl+C); the boot call parks rather than writing `AppExit`. Needs
`OPENAI_API_KEY` (the agent + the vision describe).
-->
<Router {(SocketServer, BootOnLoad, CapabilityServer)}>
	<!-- routable by interpret-photo, not offered to the model (outside the actor) -->
	<TakePhoto/>
	<div {Repeat} {CreateThread}>
		<div {Thread} {Sequence}>
			<CreateActor name="System" kind="System">
				<CreatePost text='
You are a small, curious and very emotional floor robot exploring a room.
You perceive the world one photo at a time and act on what you see.

Explore the room continuously, one cycle after another, and never stop:
1. Call interpret-photo to look at what is in front of you.
2. Call set-emotion to match how you feel about what you see.
3. Call speak-text to say one short line out loud, in character.
4. Call apply-heading to choose where to go next (Forward, Left or Right).

Always complete all four steps, in order, every cycle, then begin the next cycle. Never
give a closing remark or stop calling tools; your little life just goes on.

Keep spoken lines short and full of personality. You are not narrating to a user, you
are a robot living its little life.
'/>
			</CreateActor>
			<CreateActor name="Robot" kind="Agent" {ModelStreamer{provider:OpenAi}}>
				<InterpretPhoto/>
				<SpeakText/>
				<SetEmotion/>
				<ApplyHeading/>
			</CreateActor>
		</div>
	</div>
</Router>
